docs.abstract: Prompted by President Trump’s immigration order and in some cases their employer’s own past, workers seek to set limits on cooperation with the administration.
docs.snippet: Prompted by President Trump’s immigration order and in some cases their employer’s own past, workers seek to set limits on cooperation with the administration.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — As soon as President Trump signed his executive order on immigration, some of the biggest tech companies went quiet. Their executives did not sign legal briefs, brandish statements or dissent on Twitter. They strove for business as usual.

headline.main: Activism Hits Even the Less Flashy Tech Companies
headline.print_headline: Activism Hits the Older Tech Companies

docs.abstract: An alliance of about 30 companies, including Microsoft and JPMorgan Chase, has plans to standardize data gathering and tracking with software that is seen as harder to hack.
docs.snippet: An alliance of about 30 companies, including Microsoft and JPMorgan Chase, has plans to standardize data gathering and tracking with software that is seen as harder to hack.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Microsoft, JPMorgan Chase and other corporate giants are joining forces to create a new kind of computing system based on the virtual currency network Ethereum.

headline.main: Business Giants to Announce Creation of a Computing System Based on Ethereum
headline.print_headline: Companies Join to Build Blockchain Software

headline.main: An Ethnographer of Cancer Care for IBM Watson

byline.original: As told to Patricia R. Olsen

docs.abstract: A partnership with H&R Block shows IBM’s strategy for artificial intelligence: Watson will be a smart assistant tailored for specific industries.
docs.snippet: A partnership with H&R Block shows IBM’s strategy for artificial intelligence: Watson will be a smart assistant tailored for specific industries.
docs.lead_paragraph: In its first steps toward commercialization, IBM’s Watson took on grand, science-laden challenges like helping doctors diagnose cancer. But that is changing as IBM strives to build its artificial intelligence technology into a multibillion-dollar business.

headline.main: IBM Gives Watson a New Challenge: Your Tax Return
headline.print_headline: IBM Gives Watson’s Artificial Intelligence a New Challenge: Filing Taxes
